# Azure DevOps — CI/CD

Arquitectura de servicios: ver `azure-architecture.mdc`.

## Pipeline CI (`ci.yml`)

| Job | Comando | Bloquea merge |
|-----|---------|---------------|
| `lint-backend` | ruff + mypy | ✅ |
| `test-backend` | pytest --cov-fail-under=80 | ✅ |
| `lint-web` | eslint | ✅ |
| `test-web` | vitest --coverage ≥70% | ✅ |
| `test-infra` | bicep build/lint | ✅ |
| `test-docker` | compose config + docker build | ✅ |
| `build-web` | npm run build | ✅ |

Orden: lint → tests → build. Deploy solo si CI verde.

## Deploy workflows

| Workflow | Trigger |
|----------|---------|
| `deploy-backend.yml` | push main |
| `deploy-web.yml` | push main |
| `infra.yml` | manual |

Post-deploy smoke: ver `infra-testing.mdc`.

## Secretos

- Local: `.env` (gitignored)
- Azure: **Key Vault** + managed identity en Container Apps
- `.env.example` solo nombres, sin valores

## Observabilidad

- `GET /health` obligatorio (Container Apps probe)
- Logs JSON con `transaction_id` → Application Insights

## Web search gobernada

Lista blanca dominios, timeout 5s, fallback graceful, registrar en audit trail.

## Checklist entrega

- [ ] IaC Bicep despliega todos los recursos
- [ ] CI: tests backend + web + infra + docker
- [ ] README: URL demo + `./scripts/run-all-tests.sh`

## Static Web Apps

`VITE_API_URL` en build apuntando al FQDN del Container App.
